# Styling Guidelines

## Styling Framework

This project uses **Tailwind CSS** with RTL (Right-to-Left) support via `tailwindcss-rtl` plugin.

## Tailwind Configuration

Configuration is in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js). Key settings:
- RTL support enabled
- Custom colors defined
- Custom fonts (Cairo, Manrope)
- Custom spacing and shadows

## Design Tokens

### Colors
Use design tokens from Tailwind config:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Use design tokens
<div className="bg-primary text-text-main">
  <button className="bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover">
    Click me
  </button>
</div>

// ❌ BAD: Hardcoded colors
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#f4c430' }}>
  <button style={{ backgroundColor: '#e0b320' }}>
    Click me
  </button>
</div>
```

### Available Color Tokens
- `primary` / `primary-hover` - Primary brand color
- `background-light` / `background-dark` - Background colors
- `text-main` / `text-muted` - Text colors
- `bg-main` / `bg-card` - Background utilities

## RTL Support

The project supports Arabic (RTL) and English (LTR). Use RTL-aware utilities:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: RTL-aware classes
<div className="text-right rtl:text-left">
  {/* Automatically flips in RTL */}
</div>

// Or use logical properties
<div className="ms-4 me-2">
  {/* margin-start, margin-end - automatically RTL-aware */}
</div>
```

## Component Styling Patterns

### Utility-First Approach
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Use Tailwind utilities
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-soft">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-display text-text-main">Title</h2>
  <button className="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white rounded hover:bg-primary-hover">
    Action
  </button>
</div>
```

### Responsive Design
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Responsive utilities
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {/* Responsive grid */}
</div>
```

### Dark Mode (if needed)
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Dark mode support
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark text-text-main dark:text-white">
  {/* Dark mode styles */}
</div>
```

## Typography

### Font Families
- Use `font-display` for headings
- Use `font-body` or `font-sans` for body text
- Fonts: Cairo, Manrope (from config)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Use font utilities
<h1 className="font-display text-3xl font-bold">Heading</h1>
<p className="font-body text-base">Body text</p>
```

## Spacing

Use Tailwind spacing scale:
- `p-4` (padding), `m-4` (margin)
- `gap-4` (gap in flex/grid)
- `space-x-4` (horizontal spacing between children)

## Common Patterns

### Cards
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Card pattern
<div className="bg-bg-card rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6">
  <h3 className="text-lg font-display mb-4">Card Title</h3>
  <p className="text-text-muted">Card content</p>
</div>
```

### Buttons
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Button patterns
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white rounded hover:bg-primary-hover transition-colors">
  Primary Button
</button>

<button className="px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded hover:bg-gray-50">
  Secondary Button
</button>
```

### Forms
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Form input styling
<input 
  className="w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary"
  type="text"
/>
```

## Custom CSS

### When to Use Custom CSS
- Complex animations
- Third-party component overrides
- Global styles
- CSS that can't be expressed in Tailwind

### File Location
- Component-specific: `ComponentName.module.css` (if needed)
- Global: `index.css` or `globals.css`

## Styling Best Practices

1. ✅ **Use Tailwind utilities first** - Prefer utilities over custom CSS
2. ✅ **Use design tokens** - Use colors/spacing from config
3. ✅ **RTL-aware** - Use logical properties or RTL utilities
4. ✅ **Responsive** - Always consider mobile-first
5. ✅ **Consistent spacing** - Use Tailwind spacing scale
6. ✅ **Semantic classes** - Use meaningful class combinations
7. ✅ **Avoid inline styles** - Use Tailwind classes instead

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. ❌ **Hardcoded colors** - Use design tokens
2. ❌ **Inline styles** - Use Tailwind classes
3. ❌ **Not considering RTL** - Always test RTL layout
4. ❌ **Inconsistent spacing** - Use Tailwind scale
5. ❌ **Too many custom CSS files** - Prefer Tailwind utilities
6. ❌ **Not responsive** - Always make responsive

## Component Styling Example

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Complete component with proper styling
export function TeacherCard({ teacher }: Props) {
  return (
    <div className="bg-bg-card rounded-lg shadow-soft p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div className="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <img 
          src={teacher.photo} 
          alt={teacher.name}
          className="w-16 h-16 rounded-full object-cover"
        />
        <div>
          <h3 className="font-display text-lg text-text-main">{teacher.name}</h3>
          <p className="text-sm text-text-muted">{teacher.specialization}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <span className="text-primary font-semibold">
          {formatCurrency(teacher.hourlyRate, teacher.currency)}
        </span>
        <button className="px-4 py-2 bg-primary text-white rounded hover:bg-primary-hover">
          Book Session
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```
